        public void deleteFile(java.lang.String fileID,
              boolean phi,
              CatalyzeListener<java.lang.String> userCallback)
        Provides the ability to delete a file on the backend.
        Parameters:

        userCallback - CatalyzeListener that expects a string in response. On success a blank string is returned to this callback handler

      • getFile

        public void getFile(java.lang.String fileID,
           java.io.File file,
           CatalyzeListener<java.io.File> userCallback)
        Retrieves a file from the backend. The authenticated user must be the owner of the file or have sufficient permissions to read the file.
        Parameters:
        fileID - ID of file to retrieve
        file - File that download will be saved to
        userCallback - CatalyzeListener that expects a File in response. On success a pointer to the File is returned to the callback handler.
